			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Donna Schaper</strong></span> thinks of herself as a &ldquo;Christian socialist feminist who has a bit of a right-wing streak.&rdquo; A parish pastor in Riverhead, New York, she&rsquo;s the author of <em>Superwoman Turns Forty </em>and<em> Stripping Down: The Art of Spiritual Restoration</em>, which uses the metaphor of refinishing a chair as a spiritual art.</p><a href="/contributors/donna-schaper" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


